CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 19, 1946, pg. 1, reads: "1439 'Hits' Monday - Taking No Chances - East Liberty visitors board train as rumors of sudden street car stoppage float through the air. Hill District has no train services; probably suffered more from curtailment of trolley service than residents of any other outlying sections of the city as well as with the downtown shopping center... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Men and women boarding train in East Liberty railroad station with sign for "East Brady Local"
